Eure, Haute-Normandie, France":"Gisors, Eure, Normandy, France","France":"France","Gisors, Eure, Normandie, France":"Gisors, Eure, Normandy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Chaumont","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Gilles, Raoul, Yvon.  Spanish Alicia, Andres, Arturo, Beatriz, Elia, Jose, Julio, Miguel, Raul.","French: habitational name from any of numerous places called Chaumont ‘bald mountain’ (ultimately from Latin <i>calvus mons</i>), for example in Cher, Orne, Jura, Haute-Savoie.","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Chaumont in Orne (see 1 above)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Hugues","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Hugues Capet  (  ?938–96 ) was ruler of France (  987–96 ) and founder of the Capetian dynasty.  See  <b>Hugh</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♂ ‘Profit’ or ‘sharp’.","2  ♀, ♂ ‘Upright’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Dev ."],"variants":[{"name":"Deborah","meanings":["Biblical name (meaning ‘bee’ in Hebrew), borne by the nurse of Rebecca (Genesis 35:8) and by a woman judge and prophet (Judges 4–5) who led the Israelites to victory over the Canaanites. It has always been popular as a Jewish name. It was in use among Christians by the mid 16th century and was taken up by the Puritans in the 17th century, in part because the bee was a symbol of industriousness. Since then it has enjoyed enormous popularity, peaking in the 1960s. Among other famous bearers is the actress  Deborah Kerr  (  1921–2007 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugues II De Chaumont Sire de Gisors was born in 1097, in